  "id": "gross_profitability_ls",
  "thesis": "Point-in-time gross profitability (Novy-Marx 2013): GP/Assets = (Revenues - CostOfRevenue) / Assets, every input pulled as-of its SEC filing date via the EDGAR point_in_time_asof guard (no period-end look-ahead). Cross-sectionally rank the ~30 single-name large-caps monthly, go long the top tercile and short the bottom tercile, dollar-neutral and equal-weight, gross_leverage=1.0. Gross profitability is the cleanest above-the-line quality measure; profitable firms keep earning and the market is slow to price persistent gross margin. Used here as an honest equity SLEEVE for the risk-managed portfolio, not a novelty claim. Quarterly fundamentals -> low turnover.",
